addLiquidity(address,uint256,uint256).details: Mints liquidity with provided Dai by borrowing fyDai with some of the Dai. Caller must have approved the proxy using`controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy)` Caller must have approved the dai transfer with `dai.approve(daiUsed)`

params.daiUsed: amount of Dai to use to mint liquidity.
params.maxFYDai: maximum amount of fyDai to be borrowed to mint liquidity.

returns._0: The amount of liquidity tokens minted.

authorizePool(address,address,bytes,byte.details: Given a pool and 3 signatures, it `permit`'s dai and fyDai for that pool and adds it as a delegate

borrowDaiForMaximumFYDai(address,bytes32.details: Borrow fyDai from Controller and sell it immediately for Dai, for a maximum fyDai debt. Must have approved the operator with `controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy.address)`.

params.daiToBorrow: Exact amount of Dai that should be obtained.
params.maximumFYDai: Maximum amount of FYDai to borrow.
params.to: Wallet to send the resulting Dai to.

borrowMinimumDaiForFYDai(address,bytes32.details: Borrow fyDai from Controller and sell it immediately for Dai, if a minimum amount of Dai can be obtained such. Must have approved the operator with `controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy.address)`.

params.minimumDaiToBorrow: Minimum amount of Dai that should be borrowed.
params.to: Wallet to sent the resulting Dai to.

params.maxFYDaiIn: Maximum amount of fyDai being sold
params.to: Wallet receiving the dai being bought

buyDaiWithSignature(address,address,uint.details: Buy Dai for fyDai and permits infinite fyDai to the pool

params.maxFYDaiIn: Maximum amount of fyDai being sold
params.to: Wallet receiving the dai being bought

params.maxDaiIn: Maximum amount of dai being sold
params.to: Wallet receiving the fyDai being bought

daiForFYDai(address,uint256).details: Amount of dai debt that will result from migrating fyDai debt from Yield to MakerDAO

fyDaiForDai(address,uint256).details: Amount of fyDai debt that will result from migrating Dai debt from MakerDAO to Yield

makerToYield(address,address,uint256,uin.details: Transfer debt and collateral from MakerDAO to Yield Needs vat.hope(splitter.address, { from: user }); Needs controller.addDelegate(splitter.address, { from: user });

params.daiAmount: dai debt to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Denominated in Dai (= art * rate)
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to borrow)
params.wethAmount: weth to move from MakerDAO to Yield. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in Yield, and low enough to make sure that debt left in MakerDAO is also collateralized.

onboard(address,bytes,bytes).details: Performs the initial onboarding of the user. It `permit`'s DAI to be used by the proxy, and adds the proxy as a delegate in the controller

post(address).details: Users use `post` in YieldProxy to post ETH to the Controller (amount = msg.value), which will be converted to Weth here.

params.to: Yield Vault to deposit collateral in.

removeLiquidityEarlyDaiFixed(address,uin.details: Burns tokens and repays debt with proceedings. Sells any excess fyDai for Dai, then returns all Dai, and if there is no debt in the Controller, all posted Chai. Caller must have approved the proxy using`controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy)` and `pool.addDelegate(yieldProxy)` Caller must have approved the liquidity burn with `pool.approve(poolTokens)`

params.minimumFYDaiPrice: minimum Dai/fyDai price to be accepted when internally selling fyDai.
params.poolTokens: amount of pool tokens to burn.

removeLiquidityEarlyDaiPool(address,uint.details: Burns tokens and sells Dai proceedings for fyDai. Pays as much debt as possible, then sells back any remaining fyDai for Dai. Then returns all Dai, and if there is no debt in the Controller, all posted Chai. Caller must have approved the proxy using`controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy)` and `pool.addDelegate(yieldProxy)` Caller must have approved the liquidity burn with `pool.approve(poolTokens)`

params.minimumDaiPrice: minimum fyDai/Dai price to be accepted when internally selling Dai.
params.minimumFYDaiPrice: minimum Dai/fyDai price to be accepted when internally selling fyDai.
params.poolTokens: amount of pool tokens to burn.

removeLiquidityMature(address,uint256).details: Burns tokens and repays fyDai debt after Maturity.  Caller must have approved the proxy using`controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy)` Caller must have approved the liquidity burn with `pool.approve(poolTokens)`

params.poolTokens: amount of pool tokens to burn.

repayDaiWithSignature(bytes32,uint256,ad.details: Burns Dai from caller to repay debt in a Yield Vault. User debt is decreased for the given collateral and fyDai series, in Yield vault `to`. The amount of debt repaid changes according to series maturity and MakerDAO rate and chi, depending on collateral type. `A signature is provided as a parameter to this function, so that `dai.approve()` doesn't need to be called.

params.daiAmount: Amount of Dai to use for debt repayment.
params.to: Yield vault to repay debt for.

repayFYDaiDebtForMaximumDai(address,byte.details: Repay an amount of fyDai debt in Controller using Dai exchanged for fyDai at pool rates, up to a maximum amount of Dai spent. Must have approved the operator with `pool.addDelegate(yieldProxy.address)`. If `fyDaiRepayment` exceeds the existing debt, only the necessary fyDai will be used.

params.fyDaiRepayment: Amount of fyDai debt to repay.
params.maximumRepaymentInDai: Maximum amount of Dai that should be spent on the repayment.
params.to: Yield Vault to repay fyDai debt for.

repayMinimumFYDaiDebtForDai(address,byte.details: Repay an amount of fyDai debt in Controller using a given amount of Dai exchanged for fyDai at pool rates, with a minimum of fyDai debt required to be paid. Must have approved the operator with `pool.addDelegate(yieldProxy.address)`. If `repaymentInDai` exceeds the existing debt, only the necessary Dai will be used.

params.minimumFYDaiRepayment: Minimum amount of fyDai debt to repay.
params.repaymentInDai: Exact amount of Dai that should be spent on the repayment.
params.to: Yield Vault to repay fyDai debt for.

params.minFYDaiOut: Minimum amount of fyDai being bought
params.to: Wallet receiving the fyDai being bought

params.minDaiOut: Minimum amount of dai being bought
params.to: Wallet receiving the dai being bought

wethForDai(uint256).details: Minimum weth needed to collateralize an amount of dai in MakerDAO

wethForFYDai(uint256).details: Minimum weth needed to collateralize an amount of fyDai in Yield. Yes, it's the same formula.

withdraw(address,uint256).details: Users wishing to withdraw their Weth as ETH from the Controller should use this function. Users must have called `controller.addDelegate(yieldProxy.address)` to authorize YieldProxy to act in their behalf.

yieldToMaker(address,address,uint256,uin.details: Transfer debt and collateral from Yield to MakerDAO Needs vat.hope(splitter.address, { from: user }); Needs controller.addDelegate(splitter.address, { from: user });

params.fyDaiAmount: fyDai debt to move from Yield to MakerDAO.
params.pool: The pool to trade in (and therefore fyDai series to migrate)
params.wethAmount: weth to move from Yield to MakerDAO. Needs to be high enough to collateralize the dai debt in MakerDAO, and low enough to make sure that debt left in Yield is also collateralized.
